Module mesakit.graph.world
Package com.telenav.mesakit.graph.world.grid

Class WorldCellList

java.lang.Object
java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
java.util.AbstractList<E>
java.util.ArrayList<WorldCell>
com.telenav.mesakit.graph.world.grid.WorldCellList
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<WorldCell>, Collection<WorldCell>, List<WorldCell>, RandomAccess
public class WorldCellList extends ArrayList<WorldCell>
A list of WorldCells with convenient methods:

Cells

  • first() - The first cell in the list
  • smallest() - The cell with the smallest file size
  • biggest() - The cell with the largest file size
  • cellGraphs() - All the cell graphs for cells in this list

Graph Element Counts

  • count() - The number of cells
  • edgeCount() - The total number of edges
  • forwardEdgeCount() - The total number of forward edges
  • vertexCount() - The total number of vertexes
  • relationCount() - The total number of relations

Graph Elements

  • edges() - All edges
  • forwardEdges() - All forward edges
  • vertexes() - All vertexes
  • relations() - All relations
  • edgesIntersecting(Rectangle, Matcher) - All edges within the rectangle matching the given matcher
  • forwardEdgesIntersecting(Rectangle, Matcher) - All forward edges within the rectangle matching the given matcher
  • vertexesInside(Rectangle) - Vertexes inside the given rectangle
  • vertexesNearest(Location, Distance, RoadFunctionalClass) - Vertexes from cells in the list nearest to the given location within the given distance having the given minimum functional class
  • relationsIntersecting(Rectangle, Matcher) - All relations that intersect the rectangle and match the matcher
